<h1>Good News! Your Application Has Been Approved</h1>

<p>Congratulations! We are pleased to inform you that your application for the Maryland Accessible Telecommunications Program has been approved. You are now eligible to receive telecommunications equipment and services designed to meet your accessibility needs.</p>

<div class="alert-box">
  <h2>Application Details</h2>
  <p><strong>Application ID:</strong> <%= application.application_id %></p>
  <p><strong>Approval Date:</strong> <%= Date.current.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %></p>
</div>

<h2>Next Steps</h2>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Equipment Selection:</strong> An administrator will contact you to discuss your specific equipment needs and options available to you.</li>
  <li><strong>Delivery Arrangements:</strong> Once you've selected your equipment, we will arrange for delivery to your address or schedule pickup, based on your preference.</li>
  <li><strong>Training Options:</strong> We offer training sessions to help you get the most out of your new equipment. These can be conducted in person, by phone, or through instructional materials.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Contact Information</h2>

<p>If you have any questions or need to update your contact information, please reach out to us using any of the following methods:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>By Mail:</strong> Maryland Accessible Telecommunications<br>
    123 Main Street<br>
    Baltimore, MD 21201
  </li>
  <li><strong>By Phone:</strong> Call our customer service team at 555-123-4567</li>
  <% if constituent.email.present? %>
    <li><strong>By Email:</strong> Send messages to more.info@maryland.gov</li>
    <li><strong>Online:</strong> If you choose to use your online account, you can access your application information through our website at mdmat.org</li>
  <% end %>
</ul>

<p>Thank you for your patience throughout the application process. We are committed to providing you with the telecommunications tools you need for improved accessibility and communication.</p>

<p>We look forward to serving you!</p>
